<Content>Worst Experience Ever We chose this hotel due to it's great proximity to Dolphins Stadium. Hotel is reasonably clean and appointed, but the service was horrific.I reserved the hotel room and shuttle service to the Dolphins game online. Upon check in, the desk clerk indicated that I did not have a shuttle reservation and that they were full. I explained that I had reserved the shuttle online, she indicated that they didn't do shuttle reservations online. When I showed her my reservation confirmation that clearly indicated such, she was simply bewildered and said she was unaware of it. Another group of guests had the same problem and summoned the manager, who claimed the same ignorance. We were on our own.Fliers throughout the hotel advertised a dinner buffet (there aren't any other restaurants in walking distance, so this is your only option unless you drive elsewhere). A large group of football fans descended upon the restaurant only to find no buffet and no one to take any sort of menu orders - wait staff simply said they weren't working or said they would get to you later which never happened. When I asked the bartender for a bar rag to clear a table she was very rude and told me to go back to where I came from. Around 8pm, a buffet of brats, beans and potato salad was put out. There were only about 20 buns and all the food was gone in 20 minutes. Guests had to forage for silverware, napkins and condiments along with clearing their own tables. Folks finally took dirty silverware and washed it in the bathroom. The food wasn't bad. The bar was so backed up (but there weren't that many people) we just went back to our rooms. At about 11pm, the DJ started. We were on the 8th floor (the bar/restaurant is on the 9th floor) and the music was so loud it actually rattled the fixtures in our room. DO NOT accept a room on the 8th floor unless you plan on staying up until 1am.The breakfast situation was even worse than dinner. At 10am, the buffet was out of eggs and bacon. There was one server and he was completely overwhelmed. We could not get anything to drink - not even water. The manager from the night before finally got a pot of coffee and walked around with it, but most people couldn't even get coffee cups. He was rude and didn't even try to fix the problem. Scrambled eggs finally arrived around 10:30, but they were so undercooked that no one could eat them. It was horrible. 
