<Content>A vacation with bedbugs My family stayed at the El Palacio during a family reunion in Miami for 7/4/06. The first room we had had thick dust coming from the air conditioner, which caused my sister to have an asthma attack. We moved and the second room had bedbugs, which my sister discovered at 1:00 am. We went downstairs with the sheet and pillow case that the bugs were on and the desk attendant told us to find another hotel because he did not have anymore beds. After an hour of this, my sister, my daughter, and I decided to sleep in our rental car in the parking lot because we could not find a room at another hotel. The following day we spoke with a manager who insinuated that we bought the bugs with us, which was unacceptable since they were not in the first room and we are not unclean individuals. The third time they moved us we were supposed to have a complimentary room, but we were actually charged.The customer service in this hotel is terrible! My other family members had flying roaches in their room and the hotel did not spray nor did they move them to another room because that was the only handicap accessible room. The housekeepers did not properly clean the rooms so my father had a dirty tub from the previous guest. My other cousin had condoms in her room when she checked in and the hotel told her that they had no other rooms because they had six family reunions booked for that weekend. Staying at this hotel was a nightmare and made our 2006 family reunion very unpleasant and stressful, which is not the reason people go on vacation. 
