<Content>Worst service ever! Just returned from our 5th Anniversary trip from Michigan. Stayed at the hotel for 3 nights and four days. If it had not been a package deal, we would have left and tried to upgrade at a Motel 6.Just a list...One site of Calder Racehorse Track - they didn't know anything about the races even though they spout it in their advertising.Close to Pro Player Stadium - Advertise free shuttle to and from games; never existed and they said never will.Legends Sport Bar on site - Advertised as World Famous - 20 TV's and had to basically beg to have college football turned on during a Saturday afternoon and then they only turned on one game! Bar doesn't open until 4pm on Saturday and Sunday (biggest football days); find another sports bar for those rainy Miami afternoons.Housekeeping didn't leave towels or toilet paper after cleaning the room.Major (not minor) cockroache problem - 8 in one evening.Customer service was horrible. Not a single service person said hello or anything for that matter.If you are looking for some other place to eat, you have to travel a far distance from the hotel - there is only one place which was a Denny's and it's not in a good neighborhood. Don't travel South on 27th Ave.Will never stay there again! 
