<Content>I've been in better Econo Lodges Definitely THE worst I've experienced. From the staff, the housekeeping, the room, and especially the restaraunt.  Our first bad was the restaraunt and having to wait nearly 20 minutes before being acknowledged. The food wasn't bad, but the waiter is gone, you will not see him again. We also had a cockroach crawl up my girlfriend's leg and when she brushed it away, one of the staff just stepped on it while we were eating. The second incident at the restaraunt was at the bar that night. 2 bartenders that took 20 minutes to refill your drink, not to mention they didn't know the difference between Scotch and Bourbon. If you don't have a car, you're pretty much stuck there. It takes at least 30 minutes to an hour for a cab to arrive. The stadium is not walking distance. We almost missed kickoff. The putt-putt golf course is a joke. There isn't any turf on the concrete as shown on the brochure. The coffeemaker took 20 minutes to make one cup and they charge fifty cents a cup down in the lobby. Even Econo Lodge gives you free coffee. The front desk is very unknowlodgable of the events going on around the area and was very rude when you ask for extra things like towels, an iron, soap, etc.  The gift shop was a joke. $60.00 for a Ricky Williams jersey? I don't think so.  No free continental breakfast, the local calls are not free($75.00 deposit at .70 cents a pop, rude staff throughout the complex, free toiletries are shampoo and soap. I don't know how they call this a luxury hotel. It's an old Holiday Inn(the stickers are everywhere) that bought by some Cubans. Maybe in Cuba this is luxury. And to top if off, when we told the manager about our problems, he offered us a better room the NEXT time we came. I don't think so. 
