<Content>Dont stay here Having never visited Miami, we chose a hotel that was close to the Florida Marlins Stadium. The El Palacio Sports Hotel was the choice. It is relatively close to the stadium and that is the only benefit. Upon arrival we were told that the shuttle service to the stadium had been terminated, even though it is posted in their brochure (on their counter) and on their web page. The staff was polite and courteous. But gave the attitude that they could care less that we were there. When asked about the surrounding area and thing to see and do, they stated that they knew nothing about the area. Just for your planning purposes: This hotel is in the middle of nowhere. There is nothing around but the stadium. They have a game room and a work gym (which was closed most of the time we were there. There is also a basketball court, that was lock up. The rooms are small, not appealling, but clean. Housekeeping cleaned our room and removed all the towel. We had to repeatly ask for new towel and after 4 hours of calling finally recieved them. Guess they had to clean the ones they took in order to replace them. They have a restuarant on the top floor. They also give you the impression that they dont care if your there or not. When ordering dinner the waitress brought out one dinner at a time every couple of minute (we were a party of 5). By the time the last person in our party recieved their food the first two people were finishing. The next night we decided to try room service. They got our order wrong twice before correcting it. Upon check out the staff, as I said early, was polite and courteous but didn't care to see how our visit had been nor cared.  The bottom line...If your are going to see the Marlins or Dolphine play and want to be close to the stadium this is your hotel. Other than that I wouldn't recommend it to anyone. 
