<Author>slimGP30
<Content>Need Improvement? I just returned from the El Palacio after staying for two nights consecutively. My company contracted a two day seminar there. Well it seems to me they must be doing something right! The staff were all very courteous from the time I arrived till I left! The personel in charge of our services regarding our seminar were excellent and professional, too. They obviously know providing service with a smile goes a long way. When I recieve that type of service (even when my answer to a request is no) I can overlook little things. Once again the staff were all polite and handled themselves as professionals.In regard to my room, I found my room to be neat and clean to my satisfaction. My bedsheets and bathroom linen were clean, too. I was a little disappointed the maid had not stocked my room with a washclothe on either day, but I have no one but myself to blame because I didn't ask them to rememdy that situation! I ordered room service on the first night I was there, and it was great! They were of course courteous, prompt, and the quality of my food from Legends was excellent. The location of this hotel is a little far away from the parts of Miami area which I would vacation in (I was there for business purposes), unless of course I am predominately there for a football game or the horse races! If you are there for those two reasons, then you can't beat this little gem of a hotel! The hotel is set up very well for conferences, meetings, etc. and they have a good handle on that. As far as the theme of the hotel is concerned, however, it is geared more towards the younger to middle age crowd (like myself). It was quiet while I was there, but I stayed during weekdays. But I have a feeling that this place could get a bit rowdy on the weekend or especially if a sporting event takes place! So grandma and grandpa, you may wanna give that some thought before booking. As far as the hotel located in an undesirable area of town, I didn't notice anything really different about the area as in several other area where hotels are located. When in Miami, one needs to remember they are in a large city! As when in any large city that means to be alert, and take the necessary precautions wherever you are in the city. The hotel is located conveniently off the turnpike extension and 27th Ave. Interstate 95 is easy to access via the turnpike a few miles to the east of the hotel. In closing I would definitely consider El Palacio for a stay in the Miami area for a football game, horse race, or simply to stay in the Northern Miami/Dade and Southern Broward county areas as it is at the county line! 
